cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with fine-grained visual recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel attention-based model that uses deep learning techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Long-Short Term Memory units (LSTMs), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions person re-identification, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses an end-to-end training approach, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
